**Additional Protections**:
- **Progressive delays**: Exponential backoff (1s, 2s, 4s, 8s...) slows automated attacks
- **Account lockout**: Temporary lock after 10 failed attempts with automatic unlock
- **Security alerting**: Real-time notifications on suspected brute-force attacks
- **Audit logging**: Comprehensive logging of all authentication events for forensics
- **Step-up authentication**: Require email/SMS verification for risky logins
- **Redis clustering**: Distributed rate limiting across multiple server instances
- **Fail-secure design**: Returns generic errors, never reveals whether username exists
